# Postfix overrides appended to /etc/postfix/main.cf by docker-mailserver
# at container start (file mounted at /tmp/docker-mailserver/postfix-main.cf).
#
# Restrict outbound mail to testnet mail domains only.
#
# The check_recipient_access entry runs BEFORE permit_sasl_authenticated and
# permit_mynetworks, so the policy applies to every sender path:
#
#   * Roundcube webmail users (authenticated via SASL on submission/587)
#   * The internal docker mail-net (covered by permit_mynetworks today)
#   * External SMTP sources delivering inbound mail to local recipients
#
# Recipients matching a configured testnet mail domain are accepted with OK
# and proceed to delivery (local virtual delivery for MAIL_DOMAIN, or
# transport_maps for peer testnet mail nodes). Anything else is rejected
# with a clear 5.7.1 bounce.
smtpd_recipient_restrictions =
    check_recipient_access pcre:/tmp/docker-mailserver/testnet-recipients.pcre,
    permit_sasl_authenticated,
    permit_mynetworks,
    reject_unauth_destination,
    reject_invalid_helo_hostname,
    reject_non_fqdn_helo_hostname,
    reject_unknown_recipient_domain

# Route peer testnet mail domains to their real public IPs over direct
# port-25 SMTP, bypassing MX/A lookup. The testnet's VIP/DNAT system maps
# every VIP to a single host:port (the mail node is registered as :443),
# so SMTP cannot use VIPs -- node-to-node mail goes via real public IPs
# as documented in docs/mail-server-design.md.
#
# The map is empty by default and populated from TESTNET_MAIL_RELAYS by
# scripts/deploy.sh. Local MAIL_DOMAIN delivery does not need an entry
# here; it is handled by virtual_mailbox_domains -> Dovecot LMTP.
transport_maps = hash:/tmp/docker-mailserver/testnet-transport
